libbc-io (1.2.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat(walk): add bc_io_walk_parallel, generic parallel filesystem walk
    with callback-based filter/visit/on_error API. Extracted from the
    tool-specific walks in bc-hash, bc-duplicate and bc-seek per the
    audit 2026-04-23 Phase 4 plan.
  * Adds bc-concurrency as a new direct dependency (no cycle: bc-concurrency
    itself depends only on bc-core and bc-allocators).
  * Bumps Build-Depends to libbc-core-dev (>= 1.4.0) for the new I/O
    module (writer/reader/fmt) introduced in Phase 2.5.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 22:47:00 +0100

libbc-io (1.1.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * test(fuzz): libFuzzer harnesses for path_join and inode_set + seed
    corpora tracked in git.
  * chore(cppcheck): whitelist unusedFunction for public API in src/**.
  * chore(debian): bump Build-Depends to libbc-core-dev (>= 1.3.0) and
    libbc-allocators-dev (>= 1.2.0) to match current ecosystem baseline.
  * chore(debian): mark debian/rules executable (mode 0755).
  * No API or behaviour change.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:28:00 +0100

libbc-io (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat(dirent): add `bc_io_dirent_reader` public API — raw getdents64
    iterator with an 8 KB stack buffer, skipping `.`/`..`, returning
    {name, name_length, d_type}. Used by bc-seek, bc-hash and
    bc-duplicate to avoid the fdopendir/readdir/closedir path and its
    glibc-internal dup / fstat / fcntl probes.
  * No existing symbol changed; adds one header and one translation
    unit. Depends only on bc-core (bc_core_length).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 21:35:00 +0000

libbc-io (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release.
  * File primitives: open/close wrappers, path and inode helpers.
  * Memory-mapped file helpers (mmap / munmap).
  * Buffered stream with readahead / sequential / random advise hints.
  * Full sanitizer coverage (asan / tsan / ubsan / memcheck) and
    cppcheck-clean sources.

